  "body": "**Note:** [This truffle issue](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/534) asserts that the problem lies in using `geth --light`, so that is why I'm raising it here.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Version: 1.7.1-stable`\r\nOS & Version: `Linux svelte 4.9.52-1-MANJARO #1 SMP PREEMPT Wed Sep 27 16:40:38 UTC 2017 x86_64 GNU/Linux`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI can run `truffle migrate --reset` when running `geth --light --testnet` like I can when running with `testrpc`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ truffle migrate --reset                      \r\nUsing network 'development'.                   \r\n\r\nRunning migration: 1_initial_migration.js      \r\n  Deploying Migrations...                      \r\n  ... 0xba60d5cc8038d2013b5c72fe030b3e5713a2c64852cb26689065a9b221363445                       \r\n  Migrations: 0xd2c52206f981288e4e2fee9edcddae8601bedac9                                       \r\nSaving successful migration to network...      \r\n  ... 0x526e663bcc8099a75b397275bb940f2557dd27792fd4c5e5a4ef2617ed1d4f3f                       \r\nSaving artifacts...                            \r\nRunning migration: 2_deploy_contracts.js       \r\n  Deploying TutorialToken...                   \r\n  ... 0x2958de349a3acba76bd94c510129fdd0d9fe72c6587249e40b39244d009194b0                       \r\n  TutorialToken: 0x62b2a91ad38b864a9e7488c7881d353fa5b1673e                                    \r\nSaving successful migration to network...      \r\n  ... 0x0362d247dd7ea4f01df52a62ba217d252d2e27ef61c41b872c7fd71af469dce6                       \r\nSaving artifacts...\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\n$ truffle migrate --reset --network test       \r\nUsing network 'test'.                          \r\n\r\nRunning migration: 1_initial_migration.js      \r\n  Deploying Migrations...                      \r\n  ... 0x53c00e4aed7d9a3ec63d2583c0bb5db78b8e783fac5c027f9e1c5573d7ba0977                       \r\n/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:30432                \r\n    throw new Error('invalid address');        \r\n    ^                                          \r\n\r\nError: invalid address                         \r\n    at inputAddressFormatter (/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:30432:11)                                                                             \r\n    at /home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:35007:28      \r\n    at Array.map (native)                      \r\n    at Method.formatInput (/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:35006:32)                                                                                \r\n    at Method.toPayload (/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:35032:23)                                                                                  \r\n    at Eth.send [as getCode] (/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:35057:30)                                                                             \r\n    at Object.callback (/home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:314845:39)\r\n    at /home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:35060:25      \r\n    at /home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:316808:9      \r\n    at /home/ravi/.local/share/npm/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js:164746:11     \r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun `truffle migrate` pointing to the RPC port of `geth --light --testnet`\r\n\r\n#### Other information\r\nSee [this truffle issue](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/534)'s  investigation which purportedly shows that the issue lies in using `geth --light`.",
